    "( 3) and (4) will be considered for the timestepping procedures.",
    "Physics-informed neural networksIn the spirit of domain decomposition, parareal PINNs [326] split up the temporal domain in subdomains [t i < t i+1].",
    "A rough estimate of the solution u is provided by a conjugate gradient solver on a simplified form of the PDE starting from t 0.",
    "Ns are then independently applied in each subdomain to correct the estimate.",
    "Subsequently, the conjugate gradient solver is applied again, starting from t 1."
